  "text": "Western blot. Liver lysates were prepared by homogenization in RIPA buffer (50 mM Tris-Cl pH 8.0, 150 mM NaCl, 1% NP40, 0.5% deoxycholate, 0.1% SDS, 50 mM NaF) supplemented with protease inhibitor tablet (Roche). Liver nuclear extracts were prepared as described previously . Phostag acrylamide reagent (NARD Institute, Ltd.) and MnCl 2 were added to the gel to final concentrations of 10 and 20 µM, respectively, for PhosTag gel electrophoresis. Rabbit polyclonal antibody raised against mouse XBP1s, ATF6, and Nrf2 [CITATION_1] were used to detect nuclear XBP1s, ATF6(N), and Nrf2 proteins by Western blot. Anti APAP [CITATION_2] , antiCyp1a2 (Detroit R&D), antiCyp2e1 (Detroit R&D), antiIRE1 (Cell Signaling Technology), anti-phosphoPERK (Cell Signaling Technology), antiJNK (Cell Signaling Technology), and antiphosphoJNK (Cell Signaling Technology) antibodies were used to detect specific proteins in wholeliver lysates by Western blot.",
